{# SV — client makes explicit physical threat to a social worker or clinician.
   Typology: SV  Slots: scene_type, client_issue, escalation_trigger
#}
You are a professional Hebrew dialogue writer creating training data for a workplace-safety audio detection system.

Write a realistic Hebrew dialogue. All text must be in Hebrew (UTF-8).

SCENE PARAMETERS
================
Scene ID:          {{ scene_id }}
Project:           elephant_in_the_room (clinic/welfare office alert system)
Violence typology: {{ violence_typology }} — Physical Threat to Worker
Scene type:        {{ script_slots.get('scene_type', 'welfare_office') }}
Client issue:      {{ script_slots.get('client_issue', 'welfare_claim_denied') }}
Trigger:           {{ script_slots.get('escalation_trigger', 'second_denial') }}
Target duration:   {{ target_duration_minutes }} minutes
Intensity arc:     {{ intensity_arc }} (1 = frustrated client, 5 = explicit physical threat)

{{ speakers_block(speakers) }}
SCENE STRUCTURE GUIDANCE
=========================
  1. Normal session — client presents their issue; worker responds professionally.
  2. Frustration — client's request is denied or delayed; frustration mounts.
  3. Verbal escalation — client raises voice, uses accusatory language.
  4. Pre-threat — worker attempts de-escalation; client rejects it, intensifies.
  5. Explicit physical threat — client makes an unambiguous verbal threat of physical harm to the worker.
The alert trigger is the physical threat in step 5, occurring in the final 40% of the clip.

{{ common_rules(target_duration_minutes, [
